cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.SI 

This paper deals with matrix completion, a problem that is commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper proposes a semi-random model for the problem and investigates the performance of non-convex optimization algorithms under this model. This makes it likely that the paper belongs to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also proposes a pre-processing step that involves re-weighting the input, which could make it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
